          "type": "text",
          "name": "help_text",
          "value": "Choral counting involves a teacher leading students to count aloud together. The teacher often records each number on a board as the number is spoken. The teacher decides on a skip count amount, whether to count up or down, a number to start on, and sometimes a number to end on.",
          "_translations": {
            "value": {}
          },
